3. 養聲  
廣東話：我個人好注重養聲，所以每日都唔會喊聲到失聲。  
English: I personally pay great attention to protecting my voice, so I never scream until I lose my voice.

4. 票尾  
廣東話：張飛嘅票尾都留喺度畀我當收據。  
English: The ticket stub is still kept here for me as a receipt.

5. hacker  
廣東話：呢個 hacker 技術好犀利，連銀行嘅網絡都可以 hack 到。  
English: This hacker is very skilled; he can even hack into a bank's network.

6. 石斛蘭  
廣東話：屋企嗰盆石斛蘭好嬌貴，要每日浇水定會凋谢。  
English: The orchid at home is very delicate and needs watering every day or it will wither.

7. 吊詭  
廣東話：呢件事吊詭，聽起好似合理，但又覺得有啲唔通順。  
English: This is paradoxical—it sounds reasonable at first but feels a bit off.

8. 吊詭  
廣東話：佢講嘢吊詭，講完又反悔，無奈人哋只畀一次機會。  
English: He speaks in a contradictory way, says one thing then takes it back—people only give him one chance.

9. 各為其主  
廣東話：呢啲人各為其主，為咗自己嘅老板搏命，無所謂對方係邊個。  
English: These people are acting in their own interests, fighting for their bosses, regardless of who the opponent is.

10. 軨蓋  
廣東話：呢條路有軨蓋，車行過好嘈。  
English: There’s a tire burst on this road; the noise from cars passing is really loud.

11. 打哥夫  
廣東話：我個人好想學打哥夫，但攬不到場地。  
English: I really want to learn golf, but I can’t find a place to practice.

12. 免揀  
廣東話：呢啲蘋果免揀，買埋一袋返屋企。  
English: These apples are sold as a bag and you can’t choose individual ones—buy a bag and take it home.

13. 擺闊佬  
廣東話：佢成日擺闊佬，話自己屋企有好多錢，其實都唔係咁。  
English: He always acts like a big shot, claiming his family is super rich, but it’s not really true.

14. 廣播劇  
廣東話：每晚八點我都聽廣播劇，已經追咗好耐。  
English: I listen to radio dramas every night at 8 p.m. and have been following them for a long time.

15. 錄影機  
廣東話：呢部錄影機好舊，但仲可以正常用。  
English: This video recorder is old but still works fine.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩  
廣東話：呢張紙上面寫咗佢嘅口供，吟詩吟唔甩，唔好企硬。  
English: This paper has his confession written on it—it’s undeniable, don’t try to deny it.

17. 佈道大會  
廣東話：星期日我去咗一場佈道大會，講嘢好有勁。  
English: I attended a preaching conference on Sunday; the speeches were very inspiring.

18. 寫手  
廣東話：我識一個寫手，專門幫人寫文章，稿費好高。  
English: I know a freelance writer who specializes in writing articles and charges high fees.

19. 寫手  
廣東話：呢個寫手其實係代打，幫人代寫情書，仲有客戶認住返。  
English: This writer is actually a ghostwriter, writing love letters for others and even has clients who recognize his style.

20. 代打  
廣東話：我唔會玩呢款遊戲，請你代打幾圈。  
English: I can’t play this game, can you play a few rounds for me?

21. 茶碗  
廣東話：呢個茶碗好特別，係日本茶道嗰款。  
English: This tea bowl is very special—it’s the kind used in Japanese tea ceremonies.

22. 茶隔  
廣東話：沖茶時用茶隔，可以過濾茶渣，飲起更清。  
English: Use a tea strainer when brewing tea to filter out the leaves and make it clearer to drink.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈  
廣東話：呢啲高官做乜都無所謂，點燈都畀人罵，呢就係「只許州官放火唔准百姓點燈」嗰種雙重標準。  
English: These high officials can do whatever they want, but if an ordinary person lights a lamp, they get scolded—it’s exactly that double standard of “only magistrates can light fires, commoners can’t even light lamps.”

24. 獨唱  
廣東話：呢場演唱會有獨唱部份，個唱聲好震撼。  
English: This concert has a solo performance section; the singing was really powerful.

25. 快人快事  
廣東話：我個性就係快人快事，決定咗就會立刻行動。  
English: I’m the type who acts quickly and decisively—I make a decision and act right away.

26. 四腳獸  
廣東話：呢啲人喺公廁做野，係四腳獸嗰樣，真係好唔雅觀。  
English: These people are doing it in the public restroom—they look like those “four-legged beasts.” It’s really not decent.

27. 無米粥  
廣東話：我哋而家仲未籌備好，仲煲唔米粥，請各位先預備好心理。  
English: We haven’t made preparations yet; it’s still just “unsalted porridge without rice”—please everyone keep your expectations low.

28. 義會  
廣東話：我阿媽參加咗一個義會，每个月攤分，幫人度集錢。  
English: My mom joined a benevolent society; everyone contributes monthly to help those in need.

29. 榜文  
廣東話：呢張榜文張喺城門口，講緊今次嘅賭賭博規則。  
English: This notice is posted at the city gate, announcing the rules for the upcoming gambling event.

30. MK名  
廣東話：我見個MK名「唯愛你一世」，好肉麻，但好多人覺得夠潮。  
English: I saw an MK name “Only Love You Forever”—it’s cheesy but many people think it’s trendy. [end of text]


